WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.175
Some changes are physical. The material changes form,
shape, or position, but it is not made into a new
substance.

2
00:00:07.175 --> 00:00:14.848
Melting ice is physical. Cutting paper is physical.
Dissolving sugar is physical, because the sugar is spread
out, not rebuilt.

3
00:00:14.848 --> 00:00:19.684
A chemical change is different. In a chemical change, new
substances form.

4
00:00:19.684 --> 00:00:24.968
Chemists look for clues. Not proof from one clue, but
evidence.

5
00:00:24.968 --> 00:00:36.568
One clue is gas being made. Fizzing can mean a gas is
forming. But boiling water also makes bubbles, and that is
not the same as a new gas from a reaction.

6
00:00:36.568 --> 00:00:43.349
Another clue is colour change. If a substance changes
colour during a reaction, something new may be forming.

7
00:00:43.349 --> 00:00:51.175
A temperature change can be a clue too. Some reactions
warm up. Some cool down. The point is that energy is
involved.

8
00:00:51.175 --> 00:00:59.435
Sometimes a new solid appears inside a liquid. It may look
cloudy, or like tiny particles forming. Later we call that
a precipitate.

9
00:00:59.435 --> 00:01:08.468
Light can be a clue. Burning and some reactions give off
light. We are not doing unsafe flames here; we are reading
evidence.

10
00:01:08.468 --> 00:01:20.205
Rusting is a slow chemical change. Iron reacts with oxygen
and water. It slowly ruins things unless we protect the
metal with paint, oil, or keeping it dry.

11
00:01:20.205 --> 00:01:32.440
Indicators give another kind of evidence. A safe indicator
can change colour in acids or alkalis. That does not mean
we taste unknown liquids. Chemistry has rules because

12
00:01:32.440 --> 00:01:45.390
Now compare two changes. Ice melting gives liquid water,
but no new substance. Toast browning makes new substances,
which is why burnt toast does not unburn when it cools

13
00:01:45.390 --> 00:01:55.901
Another comparison: salt dissolving can be reversed by
evaporating the water. Rusting iron is much harder to
reverse because a new substance has formed on the metal.

14
00:01:55.901 --> 00:02:10.277
The clue checklist helps you avoid guessing from one loud
word. Bubbles, colour, temperature, light, or a new solid
can all matter, but the strongest answer explains what new

15
00:02:10.277 --> 00:02:20.668
The deepest idea is this: in a chemical reaction, atoms
are rearranged. They do not vanish. They connect in new
ways to make new substances.

16
00:02:20.668 --> 00:02:32.208
